ld War victory" failed; the public didn’t buy the official story. Lively, readable, and well-informed, this book expands current discussions about memory and history, and raises intriguing questions about popular skepticism toward official ideology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCold WarxHistoriography. 0aCold WarxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aCollective memoryzUnited States. 0aConservatismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitics and culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld politicsy1945-1989. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a20th century american history.  aamerican culture.  aamerican history.  aamerican wars.  aberlin.  abooks for history lovers.  acold war victory.  acommunism.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aend of cold war.  aend of totalitarianism.  aengaging.  afall of the ussr.  ahome school history books.  alenin.  alife during cold war.  apolitical ideology.  apolitical parties.  apolitical science.  apolitics.  apost cold war politics.  apost war life.  ared scare.  arise of totalitarianism.  arussian history.  astalin.  aunited states history.  aworld war ii.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095425040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954250/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles